<br>
Carry (level 51 Wanderer) kindly ported me to NK. As I was at the rings I was unlucky enough to be attacked by a bear and my thoughts went something like this....<br>
<br>
Oh no, not again, thought I'd outgrown the NK wildlife problem ... as long as I don't attack it the druids should leave me alone this time ... flashbacks to previous deaths at the hands of druid and treants ... which direction is the guard tower again? ... goddam Friday 13th ... wonder if I have time to call my friends ... no ... RUNNING<br>
<br>
This train of thought took somewhat less than one second and I was off, with SoW and no further sign of hits from the bear ... good. I stopped a moment to get my bearings and ... <br>
Briana Treewhisperer hit YOU for 98 points of damage...I was dead before the shock wore off, no time even to hit LOC.<br>
<br>
Back in EC I get a tell from Carry - 'BTW swarm mother is up, you may want to be careful. 'It's ok I'm safe from her' I reply, 'I'm dead already - Briana got to me first' 'Oh no - did a bear attack you? Briana did for me too when I was level 45, you were unlucky - I'll come get you' replies Carry. A kind response.<br>
<br>
So back she comes to fetch me and I'm onto my friends who are trying to locate my corpse. When Carry and I arrive at NK no sign still of my corpse, so Carry goes off to try to find it also - another great kindness. 'BTW I have a cleric friend coming to rez you' she mentions offhand. What great kindness indeed.<br>
<br>
In NK my friends comment that the zone population has suddenly increased - many of them apparently looking for my corpse, when I could give scant help to locate it except I was heading west from the rings...that awful green fog hampered everyone's attempt to find it. Carry offered to collect my friend's Necro from Tox but eventually someone did stumble across it and seent an /ooc out to say so. <br>
<br>
Adron was the kindly cleric who rezzed me and I was thereby able to regain almost all the exp I had lost. Refusing any payment, he and Carry then set off with well wishes and after bestowing amazing cleric buffs that sent my hp to over 1500.<br>
<br>
Several clerics have been praised on these pages, but not many druids ... Carry is the first in my experience and I am extremely grateful for her great kindesses and patience. <br>
<br>
All praise to Carry and Adron <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
